- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of NP-complete problems and how they can be solved using unconventional computing devices.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the operations performed within the devices, which can be related to data structures and algorithms.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the physical implementation of the devices, which can involve programming languages for controlling the signals.
